<1ST_LINE>r a PM-PierWedding     06-25 0224</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Pier Wedding,0229</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Couples Can Take The Wedding Plunge Next To Lake Michigan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Looking for a unique setting to exchange vows?
How about an old pier, complete with dramatic view of the city, a
gentle lake breeze, and a couple of fishermen and joggers thrown in
for charm?
   The city's Marriage Bureau offers the service at Navy Pier on
Lake Michigan as an alternative to the mundane civil ceremony at
City Hall.
   The $10 price won't hurt the wallet much and the view is almost
guaranteed to take the wedding party's breath away.
   ``A judge from Circuit Court marries the couples. ... It's like
getting married at the City Hall only you get married at lovely
Navy Pier,'' said Susan Wayman, who coordinates the weddings for
the Department of Cultural Affairs.
   ``You can be as elaborate as you want, within reason,'' Ms.
Wayman said Friday.
   ``I've seen six bridesmaids and flower girls'' at one wedding,
she said. ``I've seen couples arrive by horse and carriage ... and
a lot of people walk out just casually dressed. It runs the gamut.''
   The pier, which once was bustling with Great Lakes' shippers, is
frequented by athletes and anglers, so couples who marry there
should be prepared for ``fishermen sitting right next to them ...
and joggers jogging right by,'' Ms. Wayman said.
</TEXT>
