<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Door-To-DoorThief     06-25 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Door-To-Door Thief,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Alleged Thief Stops By House, Steals $70,000 Painting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An art thief who apparently knew a man wanted
to sell a $70,000 painting by Diego Rivera, went to the victim's
residence, asked a maid for the painting and walked away with the
canvas, police said.
   A Mexico City judiciary police report said the theft occurred
last Monday, but the victim, Gonzalo Faustino Gonzalez, didn't find
out about it until Friday.
   When questioned by police, the maid claimed that a black-haired
man with a beard and dark eyeglasses rang the bell of Gonzalez's
home when he was away. The man said he had come to pick up the
painting that Gonazlez wanted to sell, the report said.
   The maid, Aurelia Delgado, said she gave the painting to the
man, the report said.
</TEXT>
