<HEAD>Floods Damage Crops, Homes, Roads In Western Ukraine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains have caused flooding that has
ruined crops, roads, homes and bridges in the western Ukraine, TASS
said.
   A report said Friday that rainfall over the past 20 days in the
western Ukraine had exceeded the average precipitation for two
months.
   The rivers Pripyat and Stokhod have burst their banks, flooding
573,040 acres planted with crops and more than 296,400 acres of
pasture for cattle, TASS said.
   Roads, bridges, dykes and buildings have also been damaged, it
added.
   It said special food supplies and youth brigades had been sent
to affected areas to help alleviate the situation and repair the
damage.
   There were no reports of any casualties.
