<HEAD>Cambodian Immigrants Jailed In Death and Skinning of Puppy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Contents may be offensive to some readers</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Cambodian immigrants were jailed
after police discovered a partially skinned puppy with its throat
slit lying in a pool of blood on the men's kitchen floor, officials
said.
   Neighbors who heard the puppy's whining as it was allegedly
being beaten to death called officers Thursday night to an
apartment in a predominantly Cambodian neighborhood, said police
Sgt. David Bauer.
   Caea Sokheng and Ou Seng K, both 32, were arrested and booked
for investigation of felony cruelty to animals, Bauer said.
   ``Well, our guys found the dead dog in the kitchen so you can
draw your own conclusions,'' the sergeant said.
   Investigators estimated the dead puppy was 4 months old. Another
puppy of similar age was rescued unharmed from the apartment, Bauer
said.
