<HEAD>Security Guard Sought In Multiple Shooting</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: INSERTS one graf after 2nd graf, `Details were..,' to UPDATE
with suspect arrested.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A security guard opened fire in the lunch
room of a water treatment company on Friday, wounding six people,
authorities reported.
   Details were sketchy, although preliminary reports suggested the
security guard was known to workers at the Micropure Co. warehouse,
where the shooting took place.
   A suspect was arrested for investigation of attempted murder
about three hours later, according to Oakland Police Sgt. Bob
Crawford. His name was not released.
   ``He just drove up in the Cadillac and got out (went in the
building) and started firing,'' said an employee who answered the
phone at Micropure. He declined to give his name.
   There were no reported fatalities, but five of the victims were
in serious condition.
   All of the victims were in the break room in the company's
warehouse when they were shot, said the employee, who did not
witness the shooting.
   Three shooting victims were taken to John Muir Medical Center in
this community about 25 miles east of San Francisco, according to
hospital spokeswoman Sandra Ryan. Three other victims were treated
at Mount Diablo Hospital, said nursing supervisor Alison Karim.
   Micropure is a distributor of water treatment equipment for
household use.
