<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Telltale Tattoos,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fugitive Arrested After Chest Tattoos Reveal Identity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ACWORTH, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A shirtless fugitive's distinctive tattoos
led him back to jail after local police identified him from an FBI
flier as a suspect wanted in connection with a burglary in Illinois.
   David Easton, 50, who had no permanent address, was arrested
Friday after a purse-snatching and car wreck in Acworth, police
Capt. Nolan Sturdivant said. He was not wearing a shirt, revealing
two tattoos on his chest, one above each nipple, saying ``sweet''
and ``sour,'' the captain said.
   ``The thing that did it was the tattoo. ... It was the first
time I had ever seen a tattoo in that location,'' Sturdivant said.
``He didn't have a shirt on, so it stood right out.''
   The captain said he recalled reading about the ``unusual''
tattoo on an FBI flier he received in February describing Easton as
a suspect in a Springfield, Ill., burglary.
