<HEAD>Singapore Naval Craft Rescues Indonesians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SINGAPORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ship from Singapore's navy has rescued 24
Indonesians off the coast of Malaysia, the Singapore Broadcasting
Corp. said today.
   Three others Indonesians were reported missing and one of the
rescued men died, the state-owned radio station said.
   The rescued men told police that their boat collided with a
vessel shortly after leaving Batam Island in Indonesia, the
broadcast said. It did not elaborate.
   They were rescued Friday.
