<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Bill Blass,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Designer's Apartment One Of Two Hit By Cat Burglar</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who allegedly broke into two luxury
apartments, including the home of designer Bill Blass, was caught
as he tried to leave a building with a backpack full of loot,
police said.
   Ronald Miller, 24, of Pennington, N.J., was arrested about 5:45
p.m. Friday and charged with burglary, said Sgt. Maurice Howard, a
police spokesman.
   Miller entered Blass' penthouse on Manhattan's posh East Side by
breaking a window and allegedly stole several items, Howard said.
Blass was not home at the time.
   He then climbed over a fence to the roof of the next building,
and entered an apartment there, removing money and jewelry, Howard
said.
   The man then moved over to another apartment, where a resident
heard the commotion and called the doorman, who called police.
   Miller's backpack contained jewelry, foreign currency and silver
dollars, Howard said, apparently all taken from the second
apartment.
</TEXT>
