<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arab protesters clashed with Israeli soldiers
outside a West Bank mosque and pelted a police van with stones in
Arab east Jerusalem, witnesses said. Police arrested nine people
and closed two Arab schools.
   In the occupied West Bank town of Nablus, a Palestinian youth
was wounded in the leg when troops opened fire to disperse
stone-throwers in the casbah, or Arab marketplace, the army said.
The youth was not identified.
   The clash followed Friday's incident in which a Jewish settler
fired on Palestinians who stoned his car in Nablus, wounding seven
