an American-born settler was stabbed in the back by a Palestinian.
   ``We must throw out a couple of thousand Arabs,'' said Elyakim
Haetzni, a right-wing Israeli lawyer and West Bank settler.
``Israel can't dry the swamp by swatting a mosquito or two.''
   Yohan Chaikeh, a computer programmer from Boston who now lives
in the West Bank city of Hebron, was attacked Friday while shopping
before the Jewish Sabbath in the city's Arab marketplace. He
suffered stab wounds in the shoulder and lower back.
   Chaikeh, 33, pulled out his gun, chased his assailant about 50
yards and shot him in the elbow, said Zeev Hever, a Jewish leader
in Hebron, about 20 miles south of Jerusalem. About 200 Israelis
live among the city's 80,000 Arabs.
   He was reported later in stable condition at Jerusalem's
Hadassah Hospital.
   Chaiken's assailant was also said to be in stable condition at
Hebron's Alia hospital. He was identified as Abdel Majid Sharawneh,
22, from the nearby village of Dura.
   The stabbing marked the second serious attack on an Israeli in
less than a week. On Sunday, an Israeli farmer was stabbed and
bludgeoned to death, bringing to four the number of Israelis killed
since the Arab uprising began Dec. 8. So far, 211 Palestinians have
died.
   The army immediately closed Hebron to traffic and clamped a
curfew on the marketplace area.
   Chaiken, who emigrated to Israel four years ago, was identified
by Israel televison as an activist of American-born Rabbi Meir
Kahane's anti-Arab Kach Party.
   In other violence Friday, an Israeli couple opened fire on young
Palestinians who stoned their car in Nablus. Israel television
filmed the incident and later showed the bearded settler firing at
the Arabs.
   Officials at the city's Al Ittihad Hospital said seven Arabs,
including two 8-year-old boys, were hit by bullets, all in the arms
or legs.
   An army spokesman said the settler's car was stoned outside the
central Mazuz Masri mosque after noon prayers. The settler got out
and fired an Uzi submachine gun, and his female companion fired as
well, the spokesman said.
