<FILEID>AP-NR-06-25-88 1159EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-ProbeQuotes     06-25 0377</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Probe Quotes,340</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Defense Probe Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments made by Washington
notables about the defense contracting investigation:
   ``You can't be down there watching several million people and
the total of all of the companies and the Defense Department every
day and what they're doing, or what phone calls they're making. And
I'm quite sure that no one would think that we should be tapping
all of those phones and listening in on conversations of everybody
just on the suspicion that someone might be out of line.'' _
President Reagan.
