<HEAD>New Chinese Fighter Plane To Be Tested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new Chinese fighter plane equipped with
advanced Italian electronics will make its first test flight next
month, an official report said Saturday.
   The A5-M fighter plane is the product of a 1986 agreement
between the Italian air carrier Aeritalia and the Nanchang Aircraft
Manufacture Corp., the official China Daily said.
   The Chinese produced the body of the plane, while Aeritalia
provided the navigation and firing control systems and other
electronic equipment, the report said.
   The plane's first test flight is scheduled for July, according
to Gao Huixian, a spokeman for the Ministry of Astronautics and
Aeronautics.
   Gao said other Chinese aircraft makers also are looking for
foreign partners to develop new planes for export.
   China sold about $2 billion worth of arms to foreign buyers last
year.
