<HEAD>Official Who Kidnapped Toll Booth Attendant Sentenced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A local official who kidnapped a toll booth
attendant because he objected to the road toll was sentenced to one
year in prison, official reports said Saturday.
   ``I made a mistake but I'm not a criminal,'' a newspaper quoted
Zhou Zhiyuan, 51, as saying.
   Zhou, director of the Transport Bureau in Baoding in Heibei
province, about 50 miles south of Beijing, was arrested last month
on charges he kidnapped a toll booth attendant on a Beijing highway
May 2.
   Reports said Zhou objected to the toll fee and dragged the
worker into his van. Zhou released the woman after driving her half
a mile down the road and forcing her to return half the one dollar
toll she had collected.
   Zhou's lawyers are appealing the sentence on grounds that the
woman levied too high a toll and illegally confiscated Zhou's
driver's license, the China Daily said.
