<HEAD>Two Drug Rings Broken</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMMAN, Jordan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 25 smugglers and seized
drugs worth an estimated $600,000 in the past two weeks, the
official Jordan news agency reported Saturday.
   It said police have seized 840 pounds of hashish and a half
pound of heroin in recent raids.
   The operation ``involved two gangs who were believed to be the
most dangerous in the region,'' said Jordan's anti-narcotics chief,
Col. Ghaleb Zou'bi.
