included ``a number of Jordanians.'' He did not elaborate.
   Zou'bi has said previously that 90 percent of drug trafficking
cases in Jordan stemmed from the kingdom being used a transit point
for drugs shipped from Turkey to Arab countries.
   He said only a tiny proportion of the drugs were smuggled in for
sale in Jordan.
