<HEAD>200 Protesters Arrested Outside Abortion Clinics</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 200 abortion opponents were arrested
Saturday after staging a sit-in at two clinics, police said.
   Members of Operation Rescue were hauled away from a building
where they said they were trying to prevent women from entering
Allegheny Reproductive Health Services and Allegheny Women's Center.
   ``Each participant signed a pledge to remain peaceful and
