<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ValedictorianCharged     06-25 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Valedictorian Charged,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Valedictorian Charged with Killing Mother, Misses Graduation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NIAGARA FALLS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school valedictorian was
charged with beating his mother to death with a baseball bat in the
early morning hours before his scheduled graduation Saturday.
   William Shrubsall, 17, was charged with murder after he
confessed to killing his mother, Marge Shrubsall, 56, said police
Detective John Donner.
   The teen-ager was to deliver the valedictory speech to
classmates at Niagara Falls LaSalle High School later Saturday but
instead was in city jail awaiting arraignment Monday.
   Shrubsall called police to the house where he and his mother
lived shortly after 3 a.m. Saturday, telling them someone had
broken in and injured his mother, Donner said.
   Shrubsall confessed to the murder during questioning at the
police department, Donner said.
   ``There were family problems for a length of time,'' said
Donner. ``They had a fight ... He just lost it, I guess.''
   A high school classmate expressed shock at the news.
   ``We can't believe this,'' said Larry Lang. ``He was really
close to his mother.''
</TEXT>
