<FILEID>AP-NR-06-25-88 2008EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-MetropolitanClub     06-25 0303</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Metropolitan Club,300</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Private Club Votes To Accept Women</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SHERI PRASSO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Metropolitan Club, the last major men-only
club for Washington's elite, has followed in the tracks of the
Cosmos Club and voted to accept women as members, its president
said Saturday.
   John D.H. Kane said the vote by the club's 15-member governing
board was taken Wednesday and members were notified by letters that
arrived in the District of Columbia on Saturday.
   ``We thought it was an idea whose time had come,'' Kane said.
``The board made a policy change to accept ladies in membership for
all categories.''
   The vote was taken just four days after Washington's private
Cosmos Club voted to accept woman and two days after the Supreme
Court upheld a New York City law aimed at requiring the admission
of women to big, private clubs where important business dealings
often occur.
   Kane refused to discuss any specifics of the vote or the
procedures for acceptance into the exclusive 2,200-member club. He
said the club's decision to admit women was not based on the Cosmos
Club precedent or other pressures.
   John F. Banzhaf III, a professor at George Washington
University's National Law Center and an opponent of sex
discrimination at private clubs, disagreed.
   ``Once the Cosmos Club made its decision, it was almost
preordained that the Metropolitan Club would have to go the same
way,'' Banzhaf said.
   Banzhaf, who filed a complaint against the Cosmos Club's
men-only membership policy last year, had taken similar action
against the Metropolitan Club on Tuesday based on a District of
Columbia ordinance stating that any club with a liquor license may
not discriminate in its membership.
   Banzhaf said his next targets under the anti-discrimination law
will be three local clubs that admit only women to full membership.
 
</TEXT>
</DOC>
