<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Italy-Slaying     06-25 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy-Slaying,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Killed in Apparent Mob Vendetta</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three gunmen in a car killed a man on a
motorcycle in Naples Saturday in what appeared to be a mob
vendetta, the Italian news agency ANSA reported.
   Ciro di Giacomo, 35, died at the scene and a companion,
Bartolomeo Cimmino, 30, was wounded and managed to flee, ANSA said.
It said the killers escaped.
   Di Giacomo had a criminal record and was believed to have ties
to the Camorra, the Neopolitan version of the Mafia, ANSA said.
   The motorcycle on which he and Cimmino were riding was stopped
when the car approached, ANSA said. One gunman fired from the car
window and two others leaped out and shot the men on the
motorcycle, the agency reported.
   Cimmino was hospitalized and was charged with failure to
cooperate with authorities after he balked at answering police
questions, ANSA said.
</TEXT>
