<1ST_LINE>d f PM-OilPrices     06-25 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0207</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Energy Futures Close Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: for Saturday PMs</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Profit-taking has ended a three-day rally in
gasoline prices, while oversupply worries brought oil futures lower.
   July unleaded gasoline contracts fell 0.15 cent Friday to close
at 50.91 cents a gallon on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   Gasoline prices fell back after having crossed the
51-cents-a-gallon level on Thursday. Traders, believing thatprice
was too high, moved in to take profits, said Madison Galbraith,
senior energy specialist with Merrill Lynch Energy Futures.
   Gasoline supplies remained tight in the Northeast, but that was
not enough to extend the rally in the gasoline pit to a fourth day,
said Peter Beutel, assistant director of the energy group at Elders
Futures Inc.
   Meanwhile, futures prices for crude oil and home heating oil
fell because of overabundant supplies, the analysts said.
   ``Any day that this market goes down, you can be sure someone
somewhere is thinking, `oversupply,''' Beutel said.
   The August contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
U.S. crude, fell 36 cents to close at $16.01 per 42-gallon barrel.
The July contract for home heating oil dropped 0.80 cent to close
at 43.14 cents a gallon.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
